itt, W.O., Snow as a factor in the winter ecology of the barren ground caribou (Rangifer arcticus) (1959) Arctic, 12, pp. 158-179; Rettie, W.J., Messier, F., Dynamics of woodland caribou populations at the southern limit of their range in Saskatchewan (1998) Canadian Journal of Zoology, 76, pp. 251-259; Rupp, T.S., Olson, M., Adams, L.G., Simulating the influences of various fire regimes on caribou winter habitat (2006) Ecological Applications, 16, pp. 1730-1743; Schaefer, J.A., Long-term range recession and the persistence of caribou in the taiga (2003) Conservation Biology, 17, pp. 1435-1439; Sharma, S., Jackson, D.A., Minns, C.K., Will northern fish populations be in hot water because of climate change? (2007) Global Change Biology, 13, pp. 2052-2064; Solberg, E.J., Jordhoy, P., Strand, O., Effects of density-dependence and climate on the dynamics of a Svalbard reindeer population (2001) Ecography, 24, pp. 441-451; Stirling, I., Parkinson, C.L., Possible effects of climate warming on selected populations of polar bears (Ursus maritimus) in the Canadian Arctic (2006) Arctic, 59, pp. 261-275; Tews, J., Ferguson, M.A.D., Fahrig, L., Potential net effects of climate change on High Arctic Peary caribou: Lessons from a spatially explicit simulation model (2007) Ecological Modelling, 207, pp. 85-98; Théau, J., Duguay, C.R., Lichen mapping in the summer range of the George River Caribou Herd (northern Québec-Labrador) using Landsat TM imagery (2004) Canadian Journal of Remote Sensing, 30, pp. 867-881; Théau, J., Peddle, D.R., Duguay, C.R., Spectral mixture analysis for mapping caribou lichen habitats in northern Quebec, Canada (2005) Remote Sensing of Environment, 94, pp. 232-243; Toupin, B., Huot, J., Manseau, M., Effect of insect harassment on the behaviour of the Riviere George caribou (1996) Arctic, 49, pp. 375-382; Vistnes, I., Nellemann, C., The matter of spatial and temporal scales: A review of reindeer and caribou response to human activity (2008) Polar Biology, 